JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South African ecommerce and pay-TV group Naspers said on Thursday its subsidiary Myriad International Holdings is exploring the possibility of an international US dollar bond offering.Naspers, Africa&#8217;s biggest listed company by market size, said its subsidiary would launch a roadshow to meet potential investors, but gave no timeframe.&#8220;Proceeds from the offering, if completed, are expected to be used for general corporate purposes and to repay MIH&#8217;s existing notes maturing in July 2017,&#8221; Naspers said in a statement.